forumNotes.author: sbaeder
forumNotes.content:
What "PE" project are you using? Please add as much info on the PE as possible. Most likely, it is due to the drivers that are installed by default, and you would need to add drivers. Are you using RAID or AHCI?   

If you are using the WIN7PE_SE project, a good thing to integrate is the drivers scripts - you can use the driver packs process (boot time adding of drivers) or the driver integration (done when PE is built). Either way, the driver packs are a good source of MassStorage drivers that can be added (as well as chipset drivers and Lan drivers, etc.  

If you still need more help, give us as much information as possible (but post larger listings like the above to a file sharing site like MediaFire)...  

![:cheers:](http://reboot.pro/public/style_emoticons/default/cheers.gif)  
Scott
